%T A396862 92,93,97,101,109,113,124,129,133,136,137,141,149,152,157,161,172,173,
%U A396862 177,181,184,188,193,197,201,205,209,213,217,221,229,233,236,237,241,248,249,253,257
%N A396862 Discriminants of real quadratic fields with trivial Pólya group.
%C A396862 The Pólya group Po(K) of a number field K is the subgroup of class group Cl(K) generated by {products of prime ideals of O_K with norm q : q prime powers}. For K being a quadratic field, it is clear that Po(K) is generated by prime ideals lying above each ramified prime, and Po(K) is an elementary abelian 2-group.
%C A396862 D = A003658(n) such that A396865(n) = 0.
%C A396862 A fundamental discriminant D of a real quadratic field K is in this sequence if and only if either D is a prime power (i.e., a prime or 8), or D has exactly 2 different prime factors and the fundamental unit of K has norm 1.
%C A396862 Contains the following numbers: 8, p prime == 1 (mod 4), 4*p (p prime == 3 (mod 4)), 8*p (p prime == 3 (mod 4)), p*q (p, q primes == 3 (mod 4)). Does not contain any of following numbers: 8*p (p prime == 5 (mod 8)), p*q (p, q primes == 1 (mod 4) such that Legendre(p,q) = Legendre(q,p) = -1). See Theorem 1 and Theorem 2 of Ezra Brown's link.
%H A396862 Jianing Song, <a href="/A396862/b396862.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396862 Ezra Brown, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1090/S0002-9947-1974-0364172-9">Class numbers of real quadratic number fields</a>, Trans. Amer. Math. Soc. 190 (1974), 99-107.
%H A396862 Jean-Luc Chabert, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jnt.2019.03.008">From Pólya fields to Pólya groups (I) Galois extensions</a>, Journal of Number Theory, 2019, 203, pp.360-375.
%o A396862 (PARI) isA396862(D) = isfundamental(D) && (D==8 || isprime(D) || (omega(D)==2 && norm(quadunit(D))==1))
%Y A396862 Cf. A003658, A396865. A396863 is the complement with respect to A003658.
%Y A396862 Cf. also A003655, A003656.
%K A396862 nonn,new
%O A396862 1,1
